  "text": "As we shift into a new season, we are also shifting into a new bout of great new releases, 24 of which the New York Times has rounded up. Some are returns to favorite, bestselling series, like Suzanne Collins’s Hunger Games; others are long-awaited returns to form, like Alison Bechdel’s latest graphic autofiction. Overall, the list is fairly varied when it comes to genre, and while it does seem to lean towards very well-known authors, there are still a few debuts (like Tilt by Emma Pattee), and there’s even the last book Toni Morrison acquired as an editor in 1983 (Fish Tales by Nettie Jones). Below is a sampling of the list: The Buffalo Hunter Hunter by Stephen Graham Jones Fish Tales by Nettie Jones Sunrise on the Reaping by Suzanne Collins Vanishing World by Sayaka Murata; translated by Ginny Tapley Takemori Great Big Beautiful Life by Emily Henry My Name Is Emilia del Valle by Isabel Allende; translated by Frances Riddle The Emperor of Gladness by Ocean Vuong Spent by Alison Bechdel My Documents by Kevin Nguyen Harmattan Season by Tochi Onyebuchi Flirting Lessons by Jasmine Guillory Tilt by Emma Pattee For the full list, visit the New York Times. Find more news and stories of interest from the book world in Breaking in Books.",
